Auto-scaling infrastructure using **Terraform** typically involves provisioning:

* **Launch Template** or **Launch Configuration**
* **Auto Scaling Group (ASG)**
* **Target Group** and **Application Load Balancer (ALB)**
* **Scaling policies** based on metrics (e.g., CPU utilization)

---

## ‚úÖ Goal: Setup Auto Scaling Infra in AWS using Terraform

Here‚Äôs a full breakdown of the setup:

---

## üìÅ 1. **Launch Template**

```hcl
resource "aws_launch_template" "web" {
  name_prefix   = "web-lt-"
  image_id      = "ami-0c55b159cbfafe1f0"  # Replace with valid AMI
  instance_type = "t2.micro"

  lifecycle {
    create_before_destroy = true
  }

  tag_specifications {
    resource_type = "instance"
    tags = {
      Name = "web-instance"
    }
  }
}
```

---

## üìÅ 2. **Target Group**

```hcl
resource "aws_lb_target_group" "web_tg" {
  name     = "web-tg"
  port     = 80
  protocol = "HTTP"
  vpc_id   = var.vpc_id

  health_check {
    path = "/"
    interval = 30
  }
}
```

---

## üìÅ 3. **Application Load Balancer**

```hcl
resource "aws_lb" "web_alb" {
  name               = "web-alb"
  internal           = false
  load_balancer_type = "application"
  security_groups    = [var.alb_sg_id]
  subnets            = var.public_subnet_ids
}

resource "aws_lb_listener" "web_listener" {
  load_balancer_arn = aws_lb.web_alb.arn
  port              = 80
  protocol          = "HTTP"

  default_action {
    type             = "forward"
    target_group_arn = aws_lb_target_group.web_tg.arn
  }
}
```

---

## üìÅ 4. **Auto Scaling Group (ASG)**

```hcl
resource "aws_autoscaling_group" "web_asg" {
  name                      = "web-asg"
  desired_capacity          = 2
  max_size                  = 5
  min_size                  = 1
  vpc_zone_identifier       = var.public_subnet_ids
  target_group_arns         = [aws_lb_target_group.web_tg.arn]
  launch_template {
    id      = aws_launch_template.web.id
    version = "$Latest"
  }

  health_check_type         = "EC2"
  health_check_grace_period = 300

  tag {
    key                 = "Name"
    value               = "web-asg-instance"
    propagate_at_launch = true
  }
}
```

---

## üìÅ 5. **Scaling Policy (Optional)**

You can add auto scaling policies based on CloudWatch metrics like CPU:

```hcl
resource "aws_autoscaling_policy" "cpu_scale_up" {
  name                   = "scale-up"
  scaling_adjustment     = 1
  adjustment_type        = "ChangeInCapacity"
  cooldown               = 300
  autoscaling_group_name = aws_autoscaling_group.web_asg.name
}

resource "aws_cloudwatch_metric_alarm" "high_cpu" {
  alarm_name          = "high-cpu"
  comparison_operator = "GreaterThanThreshold"
  evaluation_periods  = "2"
  metric_name         = "CPUUtilization"
  namespace           = "AWS/EC2"
  period              = "120"
  statistic           = "Average"
  threshold           = "70"

  dimensions = {
    AutoScalingGroupName = aws_autoscaling_group.web_asg.name
  }

  alarm_actions = [aws_autoscaling_policy.cpu_scale_up.arn]
}
```

